parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Nominative 1st Person Plural
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To go forward, go on, advance; I go before, precede. From pro and erchomai; to go onward, precede.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A ship, vessel, boat. From pleo; a sailer, i.e. Vessel.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 1st Person Plural
str2: From ana and ago; to lead up; by extension to bring out; specially, to sail away.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Assos, a port of Mysia, in the Roman province Asia. Probably of foreign origin; Assus, a city of Asia minor.
Thence, from that place. From ekei; thence.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: A strengthened form of melo; to intend, i.e. Be about to be, do, or suffer something.
To take up, raise; I pick up, take on board; I carry off, lead away. From ana and lambano; to take up.
Paul, Paulus. Of Latin origin; Paulus, the name of a Roman and of an apostle.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To give orders to, prescribe, arrange. From dia and tasso; to arrange thoroughly, i.e. institute, prescribe, etc.
Thus, so, in this manner. Or (referring to what precedes or follows).

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
To travel on foot, by land. From the same as peze; to foot a journey, i.e. Travel by land.
